Investigation of how sub-sampling interferes mean expression

Load the data

load("../data/seurat_33k_main")

Subset major cell types

pbmc33k.subset <- SubsetData(pbmc33k.merged, ident.use = c("B", "NK", "TH", "TC", "Monocytes"))
pbmc33k.subset <- BuildClusterTree(pbmc33k.subset, do.reorder = T)

rm(pbmc33k.merged)

This function subsets the expression data into the desired number of groups and applies a function (by default the mean) over each row (gene) of the subset. The resulting vector of this function is added to a matrix. So the returned matrix by default is a matrix containing the mean expression of every gene inside a sub-sample.

subset <- function(exp.data, group.count, FUN=mean, ...) {

  group.size <- floor(ncol(exp.data) / group.count)

  samples.result <- matrix(0L, nrow = nrow(exp.data), ncol = group.count, dimnames = list(row.names(exp.data), NULL))
  
  for (i in 1:group.count) {
    random.cols <- sample(1:ncol(exp.data), group.size) # Random index of number of columns
    random.sample <- exp.data[,random.cols] # Use indices for random subset
    samples.result[,i] <- apply(random.sample,1, function(row) FUN(row, ...)) # Apply the function over each row and add it to the matrix
    exp.data <- exp.data[,-random.cols] # Remove the used random data for next itteration
  }
  
  samples.result <- t(samples.result)
  samples.result <- samples.result[,order(colSums(samples.result), decreasing = T )] # Order on totals
  
  return(samples.result)
}

TH cells

Subset the TH cells, remove the blank rows and divide them up in groups of 33

th.cells <- SubsetData(pbmc33k.subset, ident.use = c("TH"))
filtered.data <- th.cells@data[apply(th.cells@data, 1, function(x) !all(x==0)),]
samples.mean <- subset(exp.data = filtered.data, group.count = 33)

Mean expression of CD3E on the 33 subsamples. The avarage expression ranges from 1.45-1.65

hist(samples.mean["CD3E",], breaks = 20)

mean.total <- rowSums(samples.mean)
#samples.mean.sd <- apply(samples.mean, 1, sd)
